title: Agnieszka Radwanska and Karolina Pliskova reach last four at Tianjin Open
text:
Agnieszka Radwanska and Karolina Pliskova reach last four at Tianjin Open 16 Oct 2015 13:02:16 
comments 
Agnieszka Radwanska and Karolina Pliskova will square off in the semi-finals of the Tianjin Open after coming through their last-eight encounters in straight sets. 
Second seed Radwanska, who could secure her spot at the WTA Finals by winning the title, had the tougher time, battling past young Russian Elizaveta Kulichkova 7-6 (7/3) 6-2. 
Third seed Pliskova needed only 61 minutes to defeat Timea Babos 6-3 6-2. 
The other semi-final will be between Serbian Bojana Jovanovski, who upset fifth seed Kristina Mladenovic 6-4 4-6 6-3, and Danka Kovinic - a 7-5 3-6 6-3 winner over China's Duan Ying-Ying. Related Sport News
